    "# Task 1: Conceptual Understanding\n",
    "\n",
    "## 1. What is the difference between \"Love\" and \"love\" in NLP?\n",
    "   - In NLP, \"Love\" and \"love\" are treated as different tokens if case normalization is not applied.\n",
    "   - \"Love\" may appear at the beginning of a sentence, while \"love\" appears elsewhere.\n",
    "   - Converting to lowercase ensures consistency and reduces vocabulary size.\n",
    "\n",
    "## 2. What happens if stopwords are not removed?\n",
    "   - The dataset becomes noisy and large.\n",
    "   - Words like is, the, and, of dominate frequency.\n",
    "   - It reduces model efficiency and may affect performance.\n",
    "     \n",
    "## 3. Two scenarios where removing stopwords is harmful\n",
    "   ### - Sentiment Analysis\n",
    "  * Example: \"I am not happy\"\n",
    "  Removing \"not\" changes meaning → \"I am happy\" ❌\n",
    "   ### - Question Answering Systems\n",
    "  * Example: \"What is the time?\"\n",
    "  Removing stopwords removes structure and meaning.\n",
    "\n",
   ## 4. Explain the difference between Stemming and Lemmatization

| Stemming | Lemmatization |
|----------|--------------|
| Cuts words roughly | Uses dictionary-based root |
| Example: "running" → "run" or "runn" | "running" → "run" |
| Faster | More accurate |
| Less meaningful output | Produces real words |
   ]
  },
